

```markdown

# Ultimate CV Generator for Majd Abualnour

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.8+-blue.svg)
![FPDF](https://img.shields.io/badge/FPDF-1.7.2-green.svg)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)

A powerful Python script that generates professional CVs in multiple formats (PDF, HTML, TXT) for Majd Abualnour - AI & IoT Engineer, Full-Stack Developer, and Tech Entrepreneur.

## 🌟 Features

- **Multi-format output**: Generates CVs in PDF, HTML, and plain text formats
- **Professional layout**: Clean, well-structured design optimized for readability
- **Dynamic content**: All CV data is centralized in a Python dictionary for easy updates
- **ATS-friendly**: Includes a plain text version optimized for applicant tracking systems
- **Interactive elements**: HTML version includes clickable links
- **Comprehensive content**: Showcases all 7 major projects with impact metrics

## 📂 File Structure

```
ultimate-cv-generator/
├── Your_Name_CV.pdf         # Professional PDF version
├── Your_Name_CV.html        # Interactive web version
├── Your_Name_CV.txt         # ATS-friendly text version
├── resumeJune15.py               # Main Python script
└── README.md                     # This documentation
```

## 🛠️ Requirements

- Python 3.8+
- FPDF library (`pip install fpdf`)
- DejaVu fonts (included in most Linux systems, or download from [dejavu-fonts.org](https://dejavu-fonts.org/))

## 🚀 Quick Start

1. Clone the repository or download the script:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/majdabualnour/Professional-Resume-Maker
   cd Professional-Resume-Maker
   ```

2. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   pip install fpdf
   ```

3. Run the generator:
   ```bash
   python resumeJune15.py
   ```

4. Find your generated CV files in the project directory:
   - `Your_Name_CV.pdf`
   - `Your_Name_CV.html`
   - `Your_Name_CV.txt`

## 🎨 Customization

Edit the `resume_data` dictionary in the script to update:

- Personal information
- Skills and technologies
- Work experience details
- Project descriptions and links
- Education and achievements

Example:
```python
resume_data = {
    "name": "Majd Adel Abualnour",
    "title": "AI & IoT Engineer | Full-Stack Developer | Tech Entrepreneur",
    "contact": {
        "location": "Gaza, Palestine",
        "phone": "+972 56 714 6842",
        # ... other fields
    }
    # ... rest of the data
}
```

